  {panel}

Sometimes the planner lays things out not quite right, or for some reason we really want to have a particular item start on a certain date (and then have the scheduler plan around it).

The Start Date right now is locked to be calculated field. Would like to have it fixable.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-430].
  {panel}

When auto-calculating the scheduler is able to schedule large stories across sprints, and it shows multiple sprints selected. However if we try to fix it to start on a certain sprint, it will not schedule past the sprint.

Would like to be able to select multiple sprints and show it the same way the calculator shows it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-126].
  {panel}

[MIGRATED from uservoice]

If we build a roadmap as a team of product managers, we often get asked "Why are we building this?" - we even ask it ourselves after some time why we prioritzed one thing over another. On bigger ideas we need to evaluate strategic fit, competitive position, unfair advantage etc. and compare it for for different ideas.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-196].
  {panel}

Our organization has a JIRA project open for every development team we have. This helps them manage their work. However when we import in stories I have to manually set every single story to the team whose project it comes from. This is very time consuming for dozens or hundreds of issues.

I would want to use the team field on the streams but unfortunately most of these teams work on the same stream, so it isn't useful.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-127].
  {panel}

[MIGRATED from uservoice]
I'd love to calculate "backwards" based on a release date and the people I have, which additional ressources I'd have to add to deliver in time. Like this, i can request these ressources from other teams or add external partners to deliver what we need. 
It's easy for one topic, but getting complicated with multiple teams and competing projects.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-134].
  {panel}

[MIGRATED from uservoice]

The way we work many times is that I need to force a specific person as the story writer but the rest of the people could be automatically assigned. It would be nice to have a way for me to specify the members by Stage whereby I could specify a specific resource for story writing but allow the tool to balance the rest.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-164].
  {panel}

Currently, under release view in report, when selecting the team the utilization will not change only the epic will change accordingly.

This is because they are filter-independent and in general the value of the utilization under release view would only change when the schedule changes, i.e., when you create new backlog items, add new team members, change the skills, etc.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-135].
  {panel}

[MIGRATED from uservoice]

In the "Create and Link Issues in JIRA Projects" dialog screen, provide the option to create a subtask for each stage defined in roadmaps, Also provide the option to check which stages should be created as a sub task. For example, we have 3 stages, design, code, test, so from a roadmap Story, I would create a story in JIRA with 3 sub tasks representing the stages and copy esitmate in roadmaps stage level to sub task level. For some stories, I know that we can jump directly to code, so I would like to only create the "code" sub task and similrly only copy that estimate over to the sub tasks.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-390].
  {panel}

When importing the data from Jira into Portfolio, all user stories which do not have an epic are being forced under defaulted new epic. This is counter productive as these stories are not released and thus are separate. Stories should be allowed to be imported unattached to epics

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-178].
  {panel}

Clicking an Initiative, Epic or Story in the Backlog should grey out items that are not related to that item or hierarchy in the mini report view at the bottom.

