  {panel}

Right now when you close a story it drops out of portfolio. 
We us a simple QA process where we re-open our issues. In this case the issue doesn't show up and change status in Portfolio again.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-440].
  {panel}

From customer:
{panel}
Calculating a scenario sometimes take a lot of time. Could be very good to see how far it had come at any given point in time (percentage complete gauge much wanted). Some planning workshops include a lot of eager managers, and it could calm them down a little to see that progress is made!
{panel}

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-97].
  {panel}

As a stream manager I want to have the option to link a stream strictly to a jira project so that the stream and its versions can only be linked to initiatives, epics and stories of that project.

There should be a project multi select field when creating a stream.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-351].
  {panel}

There is currently no way for others to comment on stories created in Portfolio during planning. Users may not want to turn these stories into JIRA tickets until they have been planned, and the lack of commenting makes collaborative work difficult.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-213].
  {panel}

It would be great to be able to use a dynamic filter or select a project and version instead of having to create an explicit filter

