  {panel}

Input as received per mail: 
"It would be really useful to be able to copy an epic and it's stories… we have many epics (architectural epics) that we want to repeat in every quarter."

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-448].
  {panel}

At the moment, when a user attempt to "Apply updates to project/s" on JIRA Portfolio, all JIRA Portfolio data overwrites the linked issues information.
Sometimes this information might not be completely synchronized and JIRA Portfolio will change, for example the actual issue Description with a blank outdated value.

It would be interesting to have a condition like "use most recent updates" to compare field values when updating the JIRA issues back.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-443].
  {panel}

Ability to reorder Epics by moving its Initiative. This would make ordering a lots of Epics under an Initiative to be easier.

Currently, the ordering need to be done separately.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-131].
  {panel}

[MIGRATED from uservoice]

We have several projects set-up in Jira for different teams (server, app, etc) so would like to link high-level roadmap items to different epics or stories within different teams projects.

There's already an option to link an issue to the different stage, we just want to link each stage to issues in different projects.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-66].
  {panel}

Team names are currently directly edited inside of JIRA Portfolio and cannot be synced with any JIRA fields. 

There should be a custom field for the team on a JIRA issue which is updated if a team is set in portfolio.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-117].
  {panel}

User would like to have JIRA Issue navigator to be able to find JIRA Portfolio statuses. This way, it'd be possible to use JIRA's excel export for more complex reports.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-439].
  {panel}

Filtering on an initiative should be possible as a drop-down filtering instead of only through the general search function in order to select very specifically only one initiative (sometimes initiatives’ names overlap, so that if you want to see the shorter named initiative, you also get the longer named initiative(s))

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-99].
  {panel}

(on) issues that block issues within the portfolio should be automatically added to the portfolio.

