  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-323].
  {panel}

At the moment, the 'Update from date' dialog suggests to set the status of work items to be 'Completed' if the linked JIRA issues have no remaining estimate left. As this behaviour is not desirable in all cases, it should be made configurable via an option in the dialog that allows these work items to remain in an 'Open' status.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-22].
  {panel}

I'd like to be able to resize the columns in the Backlog view. They are all a fixed width at the moment and I can only see the first letter of the Stream in the Release column.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-35].
  {panel}

Original cutomer input: _ "I should be able to assign multiple stories to a releases in one go. At the moment I have to select the release for all of them individually."_

Suggestion also includes bulk changes to any fields and bulk prioritisation of backlog items (i.e., select multiple backlog items and perform the desired assignment / prioritisation).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-467].
  {panel}

We assign business values for each item on the Portfolio tool as voted for by business stakeholders. Currently, we represent the integer as a pre-fix, so that we do not lose the information. 

However, actual prioritization is done via a separate sheet that creates a ratio between business value and story points to reflect importance to business stakeholders and estimated effort. 

Would be great to have the ability to add custom columns as this would allow us to prioritize better within the tool.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-219].
  {panel}

Several Atlassian plugins write their logs on separate files, which helps to easily identify messages related to those plugins:
- JIRA Agile writes to {{atlassian-greenhopper.log}}
- JIRA Service Desk writes to {{atlassian-servicedesk.log}}

It would be great if JIRA Portfolio could also have its own log file - It would help both support and customers.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-27].
  {panel}

